		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Strange Powerpak activity</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Last night I decided to play Metroid on the Powerpak. Since I have yet to find a FDS rom that works I was playing the NES version. I didn't get too far in to the game when the game reset. I wasn't too annoyed because I hadn't gone far. So, I started over. It reset again only much sooner. Then it reset several times after only a couple of steps. Finally it reset and when it came back up the levels were all garbled, I had several weapons and items, and Samus was wearing her Justin Bailey suit. After I walked over to the left a bit in the garbled world and picked up an item that looked like the morphing ball it reset again and played normally, or so I thought. After collecting 2 missle containers I went for the bombs. Only it wouldn't remember that I had collected the bombs. I could leave the room and come back and the bomb icon was still sitting on it's pedestal.  Every time I could collect it again, but I could not leave bombs and it was back again if I left the room and came back. I just thought that was odd. I hope my Powerpak isn't going bad.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


